<TABLE BGCOLOR=#ccffff WIDTH=60% BORDER=0 BORDERCOLOR=#0000ff> <TR><TD><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" SIZE="3" COLOR="#000000"><FONT SIZE=-1> <A NAME=POST496>  By <B><!-Email-!><A HREF="mailto:starkadh@cajun.net"><!-/Email-!><!-Name-!>Starkadh<!-/Name-!></A></B> on Tuesday, September 26, 2000 - 03:04 pm:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><P> <!-Text-!> Greet&#39;ns Me kin.. <BR> <BR>Wit all da new information come in from da Clan Smiths ah wanted ta puts up a bit o&#39; knoweledge ah has found out about some o&#39; the Things they is able to do now. <BR> <BR>First off be Color&#39;ed Armor <BR> <BR>When da smith gets o&#39; sufficant skill they will be able to make armor of various colors.  The color of the armor be dependent on the Dye they use. <BR> <BR>Dyes are made from extracts of various bits found on critters thru-out the realm.  And the bits can only be mixed tagether by ah Shaman Alchamist or ah Dwarven Miner, wit skill in the various toxic substances used ta break down ores and metals. <BR> <BR>Being a skilled Miner, I can do such werk easily.  The Dye extracts I can makes are then mixed in a Medium Jar. &#40;Which I can also make&#41; to make the dye used in coloring the armor. <BR> <BR>Ah be informing ye all about this because the regents to make the dye extracts appear to be rare drops.  Some rarer then others, and are VERY Valuable!  Many o&#39; the common &#40; I say common because Ive been able to find several over the course of a couple days. &#41; are selling on the market for 10pp or higher for each one..not a stack minds ye. But each item.  And a common one, that I&#39;ve been activily hunting nae dropped but 1 in 40 to 50 kills. <BR> <BR>Some of the items might be found as foraged items, Evergreen Leafs found in Greater Fay might be foraged, but Im nae sure.  I&#39;ve also found a Russet Oxide on the ground as well.  So this one might be drop and foraged.. <BR> <BR>Im nae sure if thar is a full list o&#39; items for color as yet.  Since I&#39;ve nae researched it on me magic box as yet.  But if ye see ah critter dropping someing strange picks it up and asks one the smiths. <BR> <BR>Myself I&#39;ve been collecting some the ones I knows about: <BR> <BR>Russet Oxide - small brown ration shapped object. <BR>Rust Ironoxide - Red rust smalish looking &#39;ration&#39; shapped thing. <BR>Charcoal - havent seen one yet &#40;&#42;Black&#41; <BR>Sarcoffagus Fungus - Looks like red &#39;pixie dust&#39; <BR>Evergreen leaf&#39;s - Green I guess nae seen one yet <BR> <BR>Most these things be falling on Low level mobs and I thinks they would be the more common ones. But even common they nae fall often. <BR> <BR>Dis be mostly for ye information. Myself I&#39;ve been convert&#39;n the bits I find into Dye extracts for the Smiths and pass&#39;n them out.  Dhywer was very generous and gave me some plat for da ones ah give him.  The moneys he gived me was enough ta cover me costs at mak&#39;n more for some time ta come.  So if ye finds any, I&#39;ll make&#39;m into extract for ye, free o&#39; charge.  Ye ken pass&#39;m on ta da smiths or sell&#39;m yeself. <BR> <BR>A Dye component made inta a extract shud sell for 25 to 100pp or more.  Ive not seen anyone selling extracts yet. But looking at the price being paid for regents for dyes.  The market is going to be very high until it stablizes and/or the drops become more common. <BR> <BR>Im nae sure whot the trival skill level is for a Shaman or Miner to make the extracts. My skill level is over the trival limit by a bunch Im guessing.  As a Master of that particular toxic trade. <BR> <BR>Anyway kin keeps ye eyes open and if ye see something ye nae sure about keeps it and pass it over I can tests it or hopes to have more information about da dyes soon. <!-/Text-!> <P> 
